Introduction
This is a Python implementation of the famous Indian quiz show "Kaun Banega Crorepati" (KBC).
In this game, players are asked a series of multiple-choice questions and must select the correct answer from the provided options.
The game continues until the player either answers a question incorrectly or successfully answers all the questions.

Features
Multiple Choice Questions: The game presents a series of questions with four options each.
User Interaction: Players input their answers by selecting a letter corresponding to their choice.
Scoring: Players earn points for each correct answer and can track their score throughout the game.
Feedback: The game provides immediate feedback on whether the answer provided by the player is correct or incorrect.
Game Over: The game ends when the player answers a question incorrectly or completes all the questions.


How to Play 
Run the Python script kbc.py.
Follow the on-screen instructions to answer the questions.
Input your answer by entering the corresponding letter (A/B/C/D).
Receive immediate feedback on your answer.
Continue answering questions until the game ends.
After the game, your final score will be displayed.

Requirements
Python 3.x

Usage
To play the game, simply execute the kbc.py Python script.

bash
python kbc.py

